ğŸ”¹ components/YoutubeSection.js

jsx
import "./YoutubeSection.css";

const videos = [
  {
    title: "ì§‘ì¤‘ ë…¼ë‹¨",
    url: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/KCyNIAeVHQA"
  },
  {
    title: "ì´ˆì²­ ì¸í„°ë·°",
    url: "https://www.youtube.com/embed/fM4BuCgM0CI"
  }
];

export default function YoutubeSection() {
  return (
    <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
      {videos.map((video, i) => (
        <div key={i} className="aspect-video">
          <iframe
            title={video.title}
            src={video.url}
            frameBorder="0"
            allowFullScreen
            className="w-full h-full"
          ></iframe>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

ğŸ”¹ NewsByCategory.jsx

jsx
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

export default function NewsByCategory() {
  const [newsData, setNewsData] = useState({});

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/news.json")
      .then((res) => res.json())
      .then((data) => setNewsData(data))
      .catch((err) => console.error("ë¶ˆëŸ¬ì˜¤ê¸° ì‹¤íŒ¨:", err));
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className="space-y-10">
      {Object.entries(newsData).map(([category, items]) => (
        <div key={category}>
          <h2 className="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-blue-700">{category}</h2>
          <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            {items.map((item, idx) => (
              <div key={idx} className="border rounded shadow p-4 bg-white">
                <a
                  href={item.url}
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noreferrer"
                  className="text-lg font-medium text-blue-800 hover:underline"
                >
                  [{item.local}] {item.title}
                </a>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">{item.date}</div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

jsx
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

const fallbackData = {
  "ì»¤ë®¤ë‹ˆí‹°ë‰´ìŠ¤": [
    {
      title: "ì§„ë„êµ°, ê·€ë† ì •ì±… ì§€ì›ê¸ˆ í™•ëŒ€",
      date: "2025-04-21",
      url: "#",
      local: "ì§„ë„êµ°"
    }
  ]
};

export default function NewsByCategory() {
  const [newsData, setNewsData] = useState({});

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/news.json")
      .then((res) => {
        if (!res.ok) throw new Error("404");
        return res.json();
      })
      .then((data) => setNewsData(data))
      .catch((err) => {
        console.error("ë¶ˆëŸ¬ì˜¤ê¸° ì‹¤íŒ¨:", err);
        setNewsData(fallbackData); // ì‹¤íŒ¨ ì‹œ ëŒ€ì²´ ë°ì´í„°
      });
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className="space-y-10 p-4">
      {Object.entries(newsData).map(([category, items]) => (
        <div key={category}>
          <h2 className="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-blue-700">{category}</h2>
          <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            {items.map((item, idx) => (
              <div key={idx} className="border rounded shadow p-4 bg-white">
                <a
                  href={item.url}
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noreferrer"
                  className="text-lg font-medium text-blue-800 hover:underline"
                >
                  [{item.local}] {item.title}
                </a>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">{item.date}</div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

âœ… 2. React ë Œë”ë§ êµ¬ì¡° (NewsByRegion.jsx)

ì•„ë˜ëŠ” ì‹œêµ°ë³„ë¡œ ë¶„ë¥˜í•´ì„œ ì¶œë ¥í•˜ëŠ” ê¸°ë³¸ êµ¬ì¡° ì˜ˆì‹œì•¼:

jsx
import { useEffect, useState } from "react";

export default function NewsByRegion() {
  const [newsByRegion, setNewsByRegion] = useState({});

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/news.json")
      .then((res) => res.json())
      .then((data) => setNewsByRegion(data))
      .catch((err) => console.error("ë‰´ìŠ¤ ë¡œë”© ì‹¤íŒ¨:", err));
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className="p-4 space-y-10">
      <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">ì „êµ­ ì‹œêµ° ë‰´ìŠ¤</h1>
      {Object.entries(newsByRegion).map(([region, articles]) => (
        <div key={region}>
          <h2 className="text-xl font-semibold text-blue-700 mb-2">{region}</h2>
          <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            {articles.map((item, idx) => (
              <div key={idx} className="p-4 bg-white shadow rounded">
                <a
                  href={item.url}
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noreferrer"
                  className="text-blue-800 font-medium hover:underline"
                >
                  {item.title}
                </a>
                <div className="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">{item.date}</div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

python
from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.chrome.options import Options
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import json, time

# âœ… í¬ë¡¬ ë“œë¼ì´ë²„ ì„¤ì •
options = Options()
options.add_argument("--headless")
options.add_argument("--disable-gpu")
options.add_argument("--no-sandbox")

driver = webdriver.Chrome(options=options)

# âœ… ìœ íš¨í•œ ì§€ìì²´ ì£¼ì†Œ ë¶ˆëŸ¬ì˜¤ê¸°
with open("verified_region_urls_230.json", "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
    verified = json.load(f)

results = {}

# âœ… ê³µì§€ì‚¬í•­ ë§í¬ ì¶”ì¶œ í•¨ìˆ˜
def extract_notice_links(page_source, base_url):
    soup = BeautifulSoup(page_source, "html.parser")
    links = soup.find_all("a", href=True)
    result = []
    for link in links:
        text = link.get_text(strip=True)
        href = link["href"]
        if any(k in href.lower() for k in ["notice", "gongji", "news", "bbs", "board"]) or \
           any(k in text for k in ["ê³µì§€", "ì•Œë¦¼", "ì†Œì‹", "ê³µê³ "]):
            if not href.startswith("http"):
                href = base_url.rstrip("/") + "/" + href.lstrip("/")
            result.append({"text": text, "url": href})
    return result

# âœ… ì „ì²´ ìˆœíšŒ í¬ë¡¤ë§
for region, urls in verified.items():
    region_result = []
    for url in urls:
        try:
            driver.get(url)
            time.sleep(2.5)
            region_result = extract_notice_links(driver.page_source, url)
            if region_result:
                break
        except Exception as e:
            continue
    results[region] = region_result if region_result else [{"error": "no link found"}]

driver.quit()

# âœ… ê²°ê³¼ ì €ì¥
with open("notice_links_all.json", "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
    json.dump(results, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)

print("âœ… ì „êµ­ ê³µì§€ì‚¬í•­ ë§í¬ ìˆ˜ì§‘ ì™„ë£Œ â†’ notice_links_all.json")

âœ… 1. convert_notice_to_news.py (Python ë³€í™˜ ìŠ¤í¬ë¦½íŠ¸)

python
import json
from collections import defaultdict
from datetime import datetime

# ì…ë ¥ íŒŒì¼ ê²½ë¡œ
input_file = "notice_links_all.json"
output_file = "news.json"

# ê¸°ë³¸ ë³€í™˜ ë¡œì§
def convert_to_news_json():
    try:
        with open(input_file, "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
            notices = json.load(f)
    except FileNotFoundError:
        print(f"íŒŒì¼ì´ ì¡´ì¬í•˜ì§€ ì•ŠìŠµë‹ˆë‹¤: {input_file}")
        return

    news_data = defaultdict(list)

    for item in notices:
        category = item.get("category", "ê¸°íƒ€")
        news_data[category].append({
            "local": item.get("local", ""),
            "title": item.get("title", ""),
            "url": item.get("url", ""),
            "date": item.get("date", datetime.now().strftime("%Y-%m-%d"))
        })

    with open(output_file, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
        json.dump(news_data, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)

    print(f"âœ… ë³€í™˜ ì™„ë£Œ: {output_file}")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    convert_to_news_json()

âœ… 2. news_converter_fastapi.py (FastAPI ë°±ì—”ë“œ ìë™ ë³€í™˜ìš©)

python
from fastapi import FastAPI
from fastapi.responses import JSONResponse
import json
from collections import defaultdict
from datetime import datetime
import os

app = FastAPI()

INPUT_FILE = "notice_links_all.json"
OUTPUT_FILE = "news.json"

@app.post("/api/news/save")
def convert_news():
    if not os.path.exists(INPUT_FILE):
        return JSONResponse(status_code=404, content={"error": f"{INPUT_FILE} íŒŒì¼ì´ ì—†ìŠµë‹ˆë‹¤."})

    with open(INPUT_FILE, "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
        notices = json.load(f)

    news_data = defaultdict(list)
    for item in notices:
        category = item.get("category", "ê¸°íƒ€")
        news_data[category].append({
            "local": item.get("local", ""),
            "title": item.get("title", ""),
            "url": item.get("url", ""),
            "date": item.get("date", datetime.now().strftime("%Y-%m-%d"))
        })

    with open(OUTPUT_FILE, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
        json.dump(news_data, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)

    return {"message": f"{OUTPUT_FILE} ìƒì„± ì™„ë£Œ", "count": sum(len(v) for v in news_data.values())}

âœ… ìˆ˜ì •ëœ JSX ì˜ˆì‹œ (NewsByCategory.jsx)

jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

const allowedCategories = ["ë³µì§€", "ì¶•ì œ", "ê´€ê´‘í™ë³´", "ê±´ì„¤í–‰ì •", "ì¸êµ¬ëŒ€ì±…", "ì»¤ë®¤ë‹ˆí‹°ë‰´ìŠ¤"];

export default function NewsByCategory() {
  const [newsData, setNewsData] = useState({});

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/news.json")
      .then((res) => res.json())
      .then((data) => {
        // í•„í„°ë§: ì§€ì •ëœ ì¹´í…Œê³ ë¦¬ë§Œ
        const filtered = Object.fromEntries(
          Object.entries(data).filter(([category]) => allowedCategories.includes(category))
        );
        setNewsData(filtered);
      })
      .catch((err) => console.error("ë¶ˆëŸ¬ì˜¤ê¸° ì‹¤íŒ¨:", err));
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className="p-4">
      {Object.entries(newsData).map(([category, items]) => (

jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

const allowedCategories = ["ë³µì§€", "ì¶•ì œ", "ê´€ê´‘í™ë³´", "ê±´ì„¤í–‰ì •", "ì¸êµ¬ëŒ€ì±…", "ì»¤ë®¤ë‹ˆí‹°ë‰´ìŠ¤"];

function formatKoreanDate(dateObj) {
  const week = ["ì¼ìš”ì¼", "ì›”ìš”ì¼", "í™”ìš”ì¼", "ìˆ˜ìš”ì¼", "ëª©ìš”ì¼", "ê¸ˆìš”ì¼", "í† ìš”ì¼"];
  const year = dateObj.getFullYear();
  const month = dateObj.getMonth() + 1;
  const date = dateObj.getDate();
  const day = week[dateObj.getDay()];
  return `${year}ë…„ ${month}ì›” ${date}ì¼ ${day}`;
}

export default function NewsByCategory() {
  const [newsData, setNewsData] = useState({});
  const [showArchive, setShowArchive] = useState({});

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/news.json")
      .then((res) => res.json())
      .then((data) => {
        const filtered = Object.fromEntries(
          Object.entries(data).filter(([category]) => allowedCategories.includes(category))
        );
        setNewsData(filtered);
      })
      .catch((err) => console.error("ë¶ˆëŸ¬ì˜¤ê¸° ì‹¤íŒ¨:", err));
  }, []);

  const todayStr = formatKoreanDate(new Date());

  const toggleArchive = (category) => {
    setShowArchive(prev => ({
      ...prev,
      [category]: !prev[category]
    }));
  };

  return (
    <div className="p-4">
      <div className="flex justify-between items-center mb-6">
        <span className="text-sm text-gray-600">ğŸ—“ {todayStr}</span>
        <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800">ë¡œì»¬ë“œë¦¼</h1>
      </div>

      {Object.entries(newsData).map(([category, items]) => {
        const showMore = showArchive[category];
        const visibleItems = showMore ? items : items.slice(0, 5);
        const hasMore = items.length > 5;

        return (
          <div key={category} className="mb-8">
            <h2 className="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 mb-2">{category}</h2>
            <div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              {visibleItems.map((item, idx) => (
                <div key={idx} className="border p-4 rounded shadow bg-white">
                  <a
                    href={item.url}
                    target="_blank"
                    rel="noreferrer"
                    className="text-blue-700 font-medium hover:underline"
                  >
                    ğŸ“Œ [{item.local}] {item.title}
                  </a>
                  <div className="text-sm text-gray-500">ğŸ“… {item.date}</div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>

            {hasMore && (
              <button
                onClick={() => toggleArchive(category)}
                className="mt-3 text-sm text-blue-500 hover:underline"
              >
                {showMore ? "â–² ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ ë‹«ê¸°" : "â–¼ ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ ë³´ê¸°"}
              </button>
            )}
          </div>
        );
      })}
    </div>
  );
}

âœ… ìˆ˜ì •ëœ JSX (ë ˆì´ì•„ì›ƒ 2ì—´, ë‚ ì§œ ë§¨ ìœ„)

jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

const allowedCategories = ["ë³µì§€", "ì¶•ì œ", "ê´€ê´‘í™ë³´", "ê±´ì„¤í–‰ì •", "ì¸êµ¬ëŒ€ì±…", "ì»¤ë®¤ë‹ˆí‹°ë‰´ìŠ¤"];

function formatKoreanDate(dateObj) {
  const week = ["ì¼ìš”ì¼", "ì›”ìš”ì¼", "í™”ìš”ì¼", "ìˆ˜ìš”ì¼", "ëª©ìš”ì¼", "ê¸ˆìš”ì¼", "í† ìš”ì¼"];
  const year = dateObj.getFullYear();
  const month = dateObj.getMonth() + 1;
  const date = dateObj.getDate();
  const day = week[dateObj.getDay()];
  return `${year}ë…„ ${month}ì›” ${date}ì¼ ${day}`;
}

export default function NewsByCategory() {
  const [newsData, setNewsData] = useState({});
  const [showArchive, setShowArchive] = useState({});
  const todayStr = formatKoreanDate(new Date());

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/news.json")
      .then((res) => res.json())
      .then((data) => {
        const filtered = Object.fromEntries(
          Object.entries(data).filter(([category]) => allowedCategories.includes(category))
        );
        setNewsData(filtered);
      })
      .catch((err) => console.error("ë¶ˆëŸ¬ì˜¤ê¸° ì‹¤íŒ¨:", err));
  }, []);

  const toggleArchive = (category) => {
    setShowArchive(prev => ({
      ...prev,
      [category]: !prev[category]
    }));
  };

  const categoryPairs = Object.entries(newsData).reduce((acc, cur, idx) => {
    const row = Math.floor(idx / 2);
    if (!acc[row]) acc[row] = [];
    acc[row].push(cur);
    return acc;
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className="p-4 max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      <div className="text-center mb-4 text-sm text-gray-600 font-medium">
        ğŸ“… {todayStr}
      </div>

      {categoryPairs.map((pair, i) => (
        <div key={i} className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          {pair.map(([category, items]) => {
            const showMore = showArchive[category];
            const visibleItems = showMore ? items : items.slice(0, 5);
            const hasMore = items.length > 5;

            return (
              <div key={category}>
                <h2 className="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 mb-2">{category}</h2>
                <div className="space-y-3">
                  {visibleItems.map((item, idx) => (
                    <div key={idx} className="border p-3 rounded shadow bg-white">
                      <a
                        href={item.url}
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        className="text-blue-700 font-medium hover:underline"
                      >
                        ğŸ“Œ [{item.local}] {item.title}
                      </a>
                      <div className="text-sm text-gray-500">ğŸ“… {item.date}</div>
                    </div>
                  ))}
                  {hasMore && (
                    <button
                      onClick={() => toggleArchive(category)}
                      className="text-sm text-blue-500 hover:underline"
                    >
                      {showMore ? "â–² ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ ë‹«ê¸°" : "â–¼ ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ ë³´ê¸°"}
                    </button>
                  )}
                </div>
              </div>
            );
          })}
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

function deduplicateByRegion(items) {
  const map = new Map();
  for (const item of items) {
    const existing = map.get(item.local);
    if (!existing || new Date(item.date) > new Date(existing.date)) {
      map.set(item.local, item); // ìµœì‹  ë‰´ìŠ¤ë§Œ ìœ ì§€
    }
  }
  return Array.from(map.values());
}

jsx
function getTop5PerCategory(items) {
  // ì§€ì—­ë³„ë¡œ ìµœì‹  ë‰´ìŠ¤ë§Œ
  const map = new Map();
  for (const item of items) {
    const existing = map.get(item.local);
    if (!existing || new Date(item.date) > new Date(existing.date)) {
      map.set(item.local, item);
    }
  }

  // ìµœì‹ ìˆœ ì •ë ¬ í›„ 5ê°œ
  const sorted = Array.from(map.values()).sort(
    (a, b) => new Date(b.date) - new Date(a.date)
  );
  return {
    top5: sorted.slice(0, 5),
    archive: sorted.slice(5)
  };
}

jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

const allowedCategories = ["ë³µì§€", "ì¶•ì œ", "ê´€ê´‘í™ë³´", "ê±´ì„¤í–‰ì •", "ì¸êµ¬ëŒ€ì±…", "ì»¤ë®¤ë‹ˆí‹°ë‰´ìŠ¤"];

function formatKoreanDate(dateObj) {
  const week = ["ì¼ìš”ì¼", "ì›”ìš”ì¼", "í™”ìš”ì¼", "ìˆ˜ìš”ì¼", "ëª©ìš”ì¼", "ê¸ˆìš”ì¼", "í† ìš”ì¼"];
  const year = dateObj.getFullYear();
  const month = dateObj.getMonth() + 1;
  const date = dateObj.getDate();
  const day = week[dateObj.getDay()];
  return `${year}ë…„ ${month}ì›” ${date}ì¼ ${day}`;
}

// ì§€ì—­ë³„ë¡œ ìµœì‹  ë‰´ìŠ¤ 1ê°œë§Œ ìœ ì§€ â†’ ë‚ ì§œìˆœ ì •ë ¬ â†’ top5 + archive ë¶„ë¦¬
function processCategoryNews(items) {
  const map = new Map();
  for (const item of items) {
    const existing = map.get(item.local);
    if (!existing || new Date(item.date) > new Date(existing.date)) {
      map.set(item.local, item);
    }
  }
  const sorted = Array.from(map.values()).sort(
    (a, b) => new Date(b.date) - new Date(a.date)
  );
  return {
    top5: sorted.slice(0, 5),
    archive: sorted.slice(5)
  };
}

export default function NewsByCategory() {
  const [newsData, setNewsData] = useState({});
  const [showArchive, setShowArchive] = useState({});
  const todayStr = formatKoreanDate(new Date());

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/news.json")
      .then((res) => res.json())
      .then((data) => {
        const filtered = Object.fromEntries(
          Object.entries(data)
            .filter(([category]) => allowedCategories.includes(category))
            .map(([category, items]) => [category, processCategoryNews(items)])
        );
        setNewsData(filtered);
      })
      .catch((err) => console.error("ë¶ˆëŸ¬ì˜¤ê¸° ì‹¤íŒ¨:", err));
  }, []);

  const toggleArchive = (category) => {
    setShowArchive(prev => ({
      ...prev,
      [category]: !prev[category]
    }));
  };

  const categoryPairs = Object.entries(newsData).reduce((acc, cur, idx) => {
    const row = Math.floor(idx / 2);
    if (!acc[row]) acc[row] = [];
    acc[row].push(cur);
    return acc;
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className="p-4 max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      {/* ë‚ ì§œ + ë¡œê³  */}
      <div className="flex justify-between items-center mb-6">
        <div className="text-sm text-gray-600 font-medium">ğŸ“… {todayStr}</div>
        <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-blue-800">ë¡œì»¬ë“œë¦¼</h1>
      </div>

      {/* ë‰´ìŠ¤ ì„¹ì…˜ */}
      {categoryPairs.map((pair, i) => (
        <div key={i} className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-10">
          {pair.map(([category, data]) => {
            const showMore = showArchive[category];
            const hasMore = data.archive.length > 0;

            return (
              <div key={category}>
                <h2 className="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 mb-2">{category}</h2>
                <div className="space-y-3">
                  {data.top5.map((item, idx) => (
                    <div key={idx} className="border p-3 rounded shadow bg-white">
                      <a
                        href={item.url}
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        className="text-blue-700 font-medium hover:underline"
                      >
                        ğŸ“Œ [{item.local}] {item.title}
                      </a>
                      <div className="text-sm text-gray-500">ğŸ“… {item.date}</div>
                    </div>
                  ))}
                </div>

                {hasMore && (
                  <div className="mt-3">
                    <button
                      onClick={() => toggleArchive(category)}
                      className="text-sm text-blue-500 hover:underline"
                    >
                      {showMore ? "â–² ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ ë‹«ê¸°" : "â–¼ ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ ë³´ê¸°"}
                    </button>

                    {showMore && (
                      <div className="mt-3 space-y-3">
                        {data.archive.map((item, idx) => (
                          <div key={idx} className="border p-3 rounded shadow bg-gray-50">
                            <a
                              href={item.url}
                              target="_blank"
                              rel="noreferrer"
                              className="text-blue-600 font-medium hover:underline"
                            >
                              ğŸ“Œ [{item.local}] {item.title}
                            </a>
                            <div className="text-sm text-gray-500">ğŸ“… {item.date}</div>
                          </div>
                        ))}
                      </div>
                    )}
                  </div>
                )}
              </div>
            );
          })}
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

    top5: sorted.slice(0, 5),
    archive: sorted.slice(5)

                        href={item.url}
                        target="_blank"

                        className="text-blue-700 font-medium hover:underline"
                      >
                        ğŸ“Œ [{item.local}] {item.title}
                      </a>
                      <div className="text-sm text-gray-500">ğŸ“… {item.date}</div>
                    </div>
                  ))}
                </div>

                {hasMore && (
                  <div className="mt-3">
                    <button
                      onClick={() => toggleArchive(category)}
                      className="text-sm text-blue-500 hover:underline"
                    >
                      {showMore ? "â–² ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ ë‹«ê¸°" : "â–¼ ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ ë³´ê¸°"}
                    </button>

                    {showMore && (
                      <div className="mt-3 space-y-3">
                        {data.archive.map((item, idx) => (
                          <div key={idx} className="border p-3 rounded shadow bg-gray-50">
                            <a
                              href={item.url}
                              target="_blank"
                              rel="noreferrer"
                              className="text-blue-600 font-medium hover:underline"
                            >

                            </a>
                            <div className="text-sm text-gray-500">ğŸ“… {item.date}</div>
                          </div>
                        ))}
                      </div>
                    )}
                  </div>
                )}
              </div>
            );
          })}
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

const allowedCategories = ["ë³µì§€", "ì¶•ì œ", "ê´€ê´‘í™ë³´", "ê±´ì„¤í–‰ì •", "ì¸êµ¬ëŒ€ì±…", "ì»¤ë®¤ë‹ˆí‹°ë‰´ìŠ¤"];

// ğŸ”§ ìµœì‹ ìˆœìœ¼ë¡œ ì •ë ¬í•˜ê³  5ê°œ + ë‚˜ë¨¸ì§€ êµ¬ë¶„
function processCategoryNews(items) {
  const sorted = [...items].sort((a, b) => new Date(b.date) - new Date(a.date));
  return {
    top5: sorted.slice(0, 5),
    archive: sorted.slice(5)
  };
}

export default function NewsByCategory() {
  const [newsData, setNewsData] = useState({});
  const [showArchive, setShowArchive] = useState({});

  useEffect(() => {
    fetch("/news.json")
      .then((res) => res.json())
      .then((data) => {
        const filtered = Object.fromEntries(
          Object.entries(data)
            .filter(([category]) => allowedCategories.includes(category))
            .map(([category, items]) => [category, processCategoryNews(items)])
        );
        setNewsData(filtered);
      })
      .catch((err) => console.error("ë¶ˆëŸ¬ì˜¤ê¸° ì‹¤íŒ¨:", err));
  }, []);

  const toggleArchive = (category) => {
    setShowArchive(prev => ({
      ...prev,
      [category]: !prev[category]
    }));
  };

  // ì¹´í…Œê³ ë¦¬ë¥¼ 2ê°œì”© ë¬¶ì–´ 2ì—´ ë ˆì´ì•„ì›ƒ êµ¬ì„±
  const categoryPairs = Object.entries(newsData).reduce((acc, cur, idx) => {
    const row = Math.floor(idx / 2);
    if (!acc[row]) acc[row] = [];
    acc[row].push(cur);
    return acc;
  }, []);

  return (
    <div className="p-4 max-w-screen-xl mx-auto">
      {categoryPairs.map((pair, i) => (
        <div key={i} className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-10">
          {pair.map(([category, data]) => {
            const showMore = showArchive[category];
            const hasMore = data.archive.length > 0;

            return (
              <div key={category}>
                <h2 className="text-lg font-bold text-blue-600 mb-2">{category}</h2>

                {/* ëŒ€í‘œ ë‰´ìŠ¤ 5ê°œ */}
                <div className="space-y-3">
                  {data.top5.map((item, idx) => (
                    <div key={idx} className="border p-3 rounded shadow bg-white">
                      <a
                        href={item.url}
                        target="_blank"
                        rel="noreferrer"
                        className="text-blue-700 font-medium hover:underline"
                      >
                        ğŸ“Œ [{item.local}] {item.title}
                      </a>
                      <div className="text-sm text-gray-500">ğŸ“… {item.date}</div>
                    </div>
                  ))}
                </div>

                {/* ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ */}
                {hasMore && (
                  <div className="mt-3">
                    <button
                      onClick={() => toggleArchive(category)}
                      className="text-sm text-blue-500 hover:underline"
                    >
                      {showMore ? "â–² ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ ë‹«ê¸°" : "â–¼ ì•„ì¹´ì´ë¸Œ ë³´ê¸°"}
                    </button>

                    {showMore && (
                      <div className="mt-3 space-y-3">
                        {data.archive.map((item, idx) => (
                          <div key={idx} className="border p-3 rounded shadow bg-gray-50">
                            <a
                              href={item.url}
                              target="_blank"
                              rel="noreferrer"
                              className="text-blue-600 font-medium hover:underline"
                            >
                              ğŸ“Œ [{item.local}] {item.title}
                            </a>
                            <div className="text-sm text-gray-500">ğŸ“… {item.date}</div>
                          </div>
                        ))}
                      </div>
                    )}
                  </div>
                )}
              </div>
            );
          })}
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}

@app.post("/api/news/save")
def convert_news():
    input_file = "notice_links_all_with_category.json"
    output_file = "news.json"

    if not os.path.exists(input_file):
        return JSONResponse(status_code=404, content={"error": f"{input_file} íŒŒì¼ì´ ì—†ìŠµë‹ˆë‹¤."})

    with open(input_file, "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
        notices = json.load(f)

    news_data = defaultdict(list)
    for category, items in notices.items():
        sorted_items = sorted(items, key=lambda x: x.get("date", ""), reverse=True)
        news_data[category] = sorted_items

    with open(output_file, "w", encoding="utf-8") as f:
        json.dump(news_data, f, ensure_ascii=False, indent=2)

    return {"message": f"{output_file} ìƒì„± ì™„ë£Œ", "count": sum(len(v) for v in news_data.values())}

from datetime import datetime, timedelta

def is_recent(date_str):
    try:
        news_date = datetime.strptime(date_str, "%Y-%m-%d")
        return news_date >= datetime.today() - timedelta(days=7)
    except:
        return False

for region, urls in verified.items():
    region_result = []
    for url in urls:
        try:
            driver.get(url)

def extract_notice_links(page_source, base_url):
    soup = BeautifulSoup(page_source, "html.parser")
    notices = []
    for row in soup.select("tr"):
        link = row.find("a", href=True)
        date_cell = row.find_all("td")[-1]
        if link and date_cell:
            text = link.get_text(strip=True)
            href = link["href"]
            date = date_cell.get_text(strip=True)
            if "ê³µì§€" in text or "ë³´ë„" in text:
                notices.append({
                    "text": text,
                    "url": href if href.startswith("http") else base_url + href,
                    "date": date
                })
